title: Grateful Dead Live at Sacramento Memorial Auditorium on 1972-08-12
description:
Set 1

Promised Land, Sugaree, Me & My Uncle, Bird Song, Black Throated Wind, Deal, El Paso, Tennessee Jed, Playin' In The Band, Big Railroad Blues, Cumberland Blues, Stella Blue, Jack Straw, Casey Jones

Set 2

Greatest Story Ever Told, Ramble On Rose, Beat It On Down The Line, He's Gone-> Drums-> The Other One-> Black Peter-> The Other One-> Truckin', Mississippi Half Step, Sugar Magnolia, E: One More Saturday Night

reviews.review_text: This is the one When looking for the best copy of a show, this is it for 8-12-72. Thanks to all the people who continuously keep improving the quality!
Pure smoke This is a smokin' 72' show.Phil is nice in the mix and everybody is onboard.

high grade gas = pure smoke I love the mix on this, Phil and Keith real strong, but not too much.  Second set has got the goods. From Other One onwards it's incredible, and this has to be a Top 5 Truckin', 12th gear to the max with unique jam.  The Other One sandwich and Truckin are a must have.  Rest of show is Good ol 72 dankness.
